\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S4}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {{\color {blue}\uwave {Cold-start benchmark of PanelAppRex local against a best-case }}\ac {ge} {\color {blue}\uwave {PanelApp }}\ac {api} {\color {blue}\uwave {workflow.}}} {\color {blue}\uwave {The same clinical query from case study 1 was used in both settings. The x axis shows the number of panels in each benchmark set. For each run, the same growing panel set was used in both arms. The }}\ac {api} {\color {blue}\uwave {comparator was deliberately made favourable by including the known relevant panel and then increasing the number of additional panels retrieved. (A) End-to-end elapsed time from query to final ranked result. (B) Mean number of }}\ac {api} {\color {blue}\uwave {calls required to retrieve and assemble the queried }}\ac {ge} {\color {blue}\uwave {panels before ranking. PanelAppRex local required no live }}\ac {api} {\color {blue}\uwave {calls at query time. (C) Mean number of candidate panels returned after applying the input query to the retrieved panel set. For this speed benchmark, candidate panels were counted using at least one matching query term. After 150 panels in the benchmark set, the }}\ac {ge} \ac {api} {\color {blue}\uwave {returned HTTP 429 rate-limiting errors, so larger runs could not be completed in this benchmark. }}}}{23}{figure.4}\protected@file@percent }
